Group action
If the group 
  
    
      
        G
      
    
    {\displaystyle G}
   acts on the set 
  
    
      
        X
      
    
    {\displaystyle X}
  , then we can form the action groupoid (or transformation groupoid) representing this group action as follows:

The objects are the elements of 
  
    
      
        X
      
    
    {\displaystyle X}
  ;
For any two elements 
  
    
      
        x
      
    
    {\displaystyle x}
   and 
  
    
      
